pub const SERVER_INSTRUCTIONS: &str = "session-matters controls local Helioy agent sessions through smd.\n\nUse agent_run to spawn a session, agent_list to inspect sessions, agent_get before acting on one id, and agent_delete to terminate a session.\n\nTools:\n- agent_run: Start an agent runtime through the session-matters daemon and rtmd. Supports claude and codex runtimes, headless or tmux targets, a role, a directory, a namespace, labels, and filesystem agent config resolution. The tool returns the persisted session record.\n- agent_list: List session records known to the session-matters daemon. The selector grammar is all, id:<uuid>, role:<name>, namespace:<slug>, dir:<path>, label:<key>=<value>, and label:<key> in (a,b).\n- agent_get: Get one session record by id. The tool returns an error envelope when the id is unknown.\n- agent_capture: Capture tmux pane scrollback for one selected session.\n- agent_delete: Terminate daemon owned agent runtimes selected by selector. Defaults to SIGTERM with a five second grace period.\n- agent_label: Add or remove one label on sessions selected by selector. Mutations use key=value to set and key- to remove.\n- mail_send: Send durable mail to sessions selected by selector.\n- mail_read: Read unread mail for sessions selected by selector. Reads mark messages read unless peek is true.\n- mail_check: Return the unread mail count for sessions selected by selector without draining mail.\n- mail_stop_check: Return the unread mail count for stop-hook decisions without draining mail.\n- nudge: Send an ephemeral nudge to sessions selected by selector. Tmux-backed runtimes deliver through rtmd; headless or ended runtimes return typed failure messages.\n- link: Attach runtime metadata to one unmanaged session. Daemon-spawned headless sessions link stdout logs automatically.\n- logs: Read the transcript linked to one selected session.\n- wait: Wait until a selector satisfies running, terminated, or count=N.\n- doctor: Report session-matters daemon health, LOST sessions, and runtime-matters status.\n\n## Session Control Workflow\n\nStart runtime-matters with `rtm daemon start` before `smd`; session-matters requires runtime-matters protocol 0.6 or newer.\nUse `agent_run` to start a local agent runtime through the session-matters daemon.\nUse `agent_list` to inspect live and terminated sessions.\nUse `agent_get` before acting on one session id.\nUse `agent_capture` to read tmux pane scrollback for a tmux backed session.\nUse `agent_delete` to terminate daemon owned sessions.\nUse `agent_label` to add or remove labels on selected sessions.\nUse `logs` for daemon-spawned headless transcripts, and `link` only for unmanaged sessions.\nUse `wait` and `doctor` for lifecycle and runtime-matters diagnostics.\nUse `mail_send`, `mail_check`, and `mail_read` for durable session mail.\nUse `nudge` for the ephemeral notification surface.";
